1.
URL: https://amazon.com/Double-Stainless-Commercial-Refrigerator/B60HON32?ie=UTF8&qid=142952676&sr=93&keywords=commercial+fridge

a. host: amazon.com

b. names of query parameters: ie, qid, sr, keywords

c. values of query parameters: UTF8, 142952676, 93, commercial + fridge

d. scheme: https

e. path: /Double-Stainless-Commercial-Refrigerator/B60HON32

f. port: none

2.
http://amazon.com:3000/products/B60HON32?qid=142952676&sr=93

3.
http://localhost:4567/todos/15

a. query parameters: none

b. scheme: http

c. path: /todos/15

d. host: localhost

e. port : 4567

4. One way to encode a space in a query parameter is to use it's ASCII encoded value of %20.
Another way is to use a '+' sign.

5. The '?' indicates the beginning of query parameters.

6.  A '=' sign is used between names and values of query parameters.

7. The '&' character is used between multiple query parameters.